I can remember my mother and I once went to Bishop Auckland - shopping and - we were coming back by the autocar, that's at five o'clock you see at night and - it began to snow. A
nd by the time we got out of that station - and up Lyons Bank, the snow was that deep it was drifting. I never saw anything like it in my life, it took us hours to get home. It would be nine or ten o'clock before we got home that night. We had a long - fo
u
r miles to walk you see, and - I was putting one foot down, then the other foot down and then another and that's the way we had to go, 'til we got to a row of houses. And then mother says, now come along, she says, we've done enough for the time being, we
'll ask this lady if she'll make us a cup of tea. So we went and - mother knew her you see, and - we went and knocked at the door and we told her what had happened. And she made us a nice cup of hot tea.
